  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA359-kiḷavi">itu tōḻi taḻai yēṟṟukkoṇṭu niṉṟu talaimakaḷ kuṟippi ṉōṭiyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante shied away from HER intention, standing [there] after having received a leaf [skirt].</p>
        </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA359">
<l>            cilampiṉ mēynta ciṟukōṭṭuc cētā</l>
<l>            valaṅkukulaik kānta ṭīṇṭit tātukak</l>
<l>            kaṉṟutāy maruḷuṅ kuṉṟa nāṭa</l>
<l>            ṉuṭukkun taḻaitan taṉaṉē yavaiyā</l>
<l>            muṭuppiṉ yāyañ cutumē koṭuppiṟ</l>
<l>            kēḷuṭaik kēṭañ cutumē yāyiṭai</l>
<l>            vāṭala kollō tāmē yavaṉmalaip</l>
<l>            pōruṭai varuṭaiyum pāyāc</l>
<l>            cūruṭai yaṭukkatta koyaṟkarun taḻaiyē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>            The man from a land of hills, where the calf is confused about [its] mother,</l>
<l rend="indent">            when pollen was shed, from touching the Malabar lily in swaying bunches,</l>
<l rend="indent2">            on the red cow with small horns that grazed on the mountain side,</l>
<l>        he gave [us] foliage to put on.</l>
<l rend="indent4">            If we put on</l>
<l>        those, I fear mother.</l>
<l rend="indent4">            If we give [them back],</l>
<l>        I fear the loss of a friend<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kēḷ-uṭai</term> is an incomprehensible case marker here (if it can be regarded as such), but the variant <term xml:lang="ta">kēḷiṭai</term> (at best to be understood as a loc. suffix) is equally incomprehensible.</note>.</l>
<l rend="indent4">            In the meantime,</l>
<l>        won’t they themselves fade,</l>
<l rend="indent">            the leaves difficult to pluck from the fearful mountain-side,</l>
<l rend="indent2">            where even the belligerent Varuṭai sheep do not jump,</l>
<l>            on his mountain?</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
